# Overview

- We read accelerometer sensor data from our mobile phone.
- Then, we are sending this data to a Raspberry Pi device that is present on the local network using MQTT protocol.
- The agenda is to analyze the data in real-time to count the number of reps of curls a person is doing.
- Paralelly we also log the recieved data on the Raspberry Pi.

# MQTT

Mqtt is one of the standard messaging protocols for the Internet of Things(IoT). It is designed for connecting remote devices with minimal bandwidth.

## Publish/Subscribe Architecture

MQTT protocol follows a publish/subscribe architecture.
There will be a Broker on a local network or in the cloud based on our requirement.(server).
